definition: ten (used in fractions, writing checks etc)/assorted/miscellaneous
suffix, used to form interrogative 什麼|什么[shen2 me5], what?, indefinite 這麼|这么[zhe4 me5] thus, etc

sentences.english: Scientists don't yet know what the effects of those reactions might be.
sentences.chinese: 科学家们还不清楚这些反应会具体产生什么样的结果。

sentences.english: What kind of government will bel behind for his successor?
sentences.chinese: 他将留给后任一个什么样的政府呢？

sentences.english: What kind of work experience dob you have?
What do we expect from the people who develop our software?
sentences.chinese: 我们对为我们开发软件的人都有着什么样的期望呢？

sentences.english: What were your expectations before and after taking the course?
sentences.chinese: 您在学习这门课程前后曾有什么样的期望？

sentences.english: What kind of Gundam story are you aiming for?
sentences.chinese: 你想做一个什么样的高达故事？

sentences.english: I: What experience have you had that qualifies you for this position?
sentences.chinese: 你有什么样的经验能使你胜任这个职位？

sentences.english: What was the tributary system and how will it shape China's future behaviour?
sentences.chinese: 到底什么是纳贡体制，它将使中国成为什么样的国家？

sentences.english: What kind of hotel would you like, five-star or something simpler?
sentences.chinese: 您愿意要什么样的酒店，五星级的还是普通些的？

sentences.english: The demand of the teacher what kind of teach a research?
sentences.chinese: 教师需要什么样的教科研？

sentences.english: What sort of farewell is that?
What is the Battle Between the Dragon and the Tiger?
sentences.chinese: 龙虎斗是一道什么样的菜？

sentences.english: What will it generate with the combination of wood and metal?
sentences.chinese: 当木与金属的组合会产生什么样的效果？

sentences.english: So what kind of an executive makes for an ideal white knight?
sentences.chinese: 那么，什么样的经理人才是理想的白衣骑士呢？

sentences.english: No one knows what regulations apply to crypto-equity yet.
sentences.chinese: 没有人知道什么样的法规能适用于加密股权。

sentences.english: Well, you know what a canadian chipmunk looks like?
sentences.chinese: 那你知道一只加拿大花栗鼠长什么样儿的吗？

definition: how?/how about?/how was it?/how are things?
to go to the bottom of a matter/after all/when all is said and done/(in an interrogative sentence) finally/outcome/result
finally/in the end/when all is said and done/after all/to the end/to the last
how old?/how big?/how much?/so big/that much

particle indicating that a previously asked question is to be applied to the preceding word ("What about ...?", "And ...?")/particle for inquiring about location ("Where is ...?")/particle signaling a pause, to emphasize the preceding words and allow the listener time to take them on board ("ok?", "are you with me?")/(at the end of a declarative sentence) particle indicating continuation of a state or action/particle indicating strong affirmation
(before a noun) Do (you, they etc) have ...?/Is there a ...?/(before a verb) Did (you, they etc) (verb, infinitive)?/Have (you, they etc) (verb, past participle)?
variant of 怎麼|怎么[zen3 me5]
how much?/how many?/(phone number, student ID etc) what number?
